lumbia provides a thoughtful critical analysis of the role of social justice, human capital, and the market in the development of the institutional arrangements – the distribution of institutions by size, mission, type, and location – and policies that have shaped contemporary education in the province.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPostsecondary educationzBritish ColumbiaxHistory. 0aUniversities and collegeszBritish ColumbiaxHistory. 7aEDUCATION / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311141792940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483835140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774838351423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774838351/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-141792-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles